{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863376984,"sessionID":"ses_2864be159ffehrySNsT9JNg1Wc","part":{"id":"prt_d79b4a617001OfpKmnzCL2I1RS","messageID":"msg_d79b48bad001B5VKnO9h40X6FO","sessionID":"ses_2864be159ffehrySNsT9JNg1Wc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_363c5d1d37304440b115f875","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/agentd` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Configuration Structure (`config.go`)\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n18:   - Define package `agentd` with required imports\n19: \n20: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `CleanupConfig` struct in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n21:   - Fields: `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CleanupInterval time.Duration`, `MaxConcurrentCleanups int`, `Enabled bool`, `DryRun bool`, `NamespaceAllowList []string`, `NamespaceDenyList []string`\n22: \n23: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Implement `DefaultCleanupConfig() *CleanupConfig` in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n24:   - Return config with: AgentRuntime timeout 30m, CodeInterpreter timeout 15m, interval 5m, max concurrent 10, enabled true, dry run false\n25: \n26: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Implement `LoadCleanupConfigFromEnv() (*CleanupConfig, error)` in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n27:   - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED` (default: true)\n28:   - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_DRY_RUN` (default: false)\n29:   - Load `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT` (default: 30m)\n30:   - Load `AGENTD_CODE_INTERPRETER_IDLE_TIMEOUT` (default: 15m)\n31:   - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL` (default: 5m)\n32:   - Load `AGENTD_MAX_CONCURRENT_CLEANUPS` (default: 10)\n33:   - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST` (comma-separated, default: empty)\n34:   - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_DENY_LIST` (default: kube-system,kube-public)\n35:   - Parse duration strings, log warnings and use defaults on parse failures\n36: \n37: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `Validate(c *CleanupConfig) error` in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n38:   - Validate timeouts are positive\n39:   - Validate CleanupInterval is positive\n40:   - Validate MaxConcurrentCleanups > 0\n41:   - Validate NamespaceDenyList includes system namespaces\n42: \n43: ### Phase 2: CleanupError Types (`errors.go`)\n44: \n45: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Define `CleanupErrorType` type and constants in `pkg/agentd/errors.go`\n46:   - Type: `CleanupErrorType` (string alias)\n47:   - Constants: `CleanupErrorNotFound`, `CleanupErrorPermission`, `CleanupErrorTimeout`, `CleanupErrorConflict`, `CleanupErrorUnknown`\n48: \n49: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Define `CleanupError` struct in `pkg/agentd/errors.go`\n50:   - Fields: `Type CleanupErrorType`, `ResourceKind string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`, `Message string`, `Underlying error`\n51:   - Method: `Error() string` with format \"cleanup error [%s] for %s/%s/%s: %s\"\n52: \n53: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `NewCleanupError(errType CleanupErrorType, kind, namespace, name, message string, underlying error) *CleanupError` in `pkg/agentd/errors.go`\n54: \n55: ### Phase 3: IdleTracker Interface and Implementation (`idle_tracker.go`)\n56: \n57: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Define `ResourceKey` struct in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n58:   - Fields: `Kind string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`\n59: \n60: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Define `IdleTracker` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n61:   - Methods: `UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time)`, `GetLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string) (time.Time, bool)`, `IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool`, `Remove(kind, namespace, name string)`, `ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey`\n62: \n63: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Define `idleTracker` struct in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n64:   - Fields: `mu sync.RWMutex`, `lastActivity map[ResourceKey]time.Time`, `logger klog.Logger`\n65: \n66: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `NewIdleTracker(logger klog.Logger) IdleTracker` in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n67:   - Initialize lastActivity map\n68:   - Return initialized tracker\n69: \n70: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `UpdateLastActivity` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n71:   - Lock mutex, update map, log at V(4)\n72: \n73: - [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `GetLastActivity` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n74:   - RLock mutex, return timestamp and exists bool\n75: \n76: - [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `IsIdle` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n77:   - Return true if no activity recorded\n78:   - Return true if time.Since(lastActivity) >= timeout\n79:   - Return false otherwise\n80: \n81: - [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `Remove` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n82:   - Lock mutex, delete from map\n83: \n84: - [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `ListIdleResources` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n85:   - RLock mutex, iterate map, collect idle resources\n86: \n87: ### Phase 4: CleanupMetrics (`cleanup_metrics.go`)\n88: \n89: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Define `CleanupMetrics` struct in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n90:   - Fields: `agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter`, `codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter`, `cleanupErrorsTotal *prometheus.CounterVec`, `cleanupDurationSeconds *prometheus.HistogramVec`, `idleResourcesDetected *prometheus.GaugeVec`\n91: \n92: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewCleanupMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer) *CleanupMetrics` in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n93:   - Initialize all metrics with proper labels\n94:   - Register metrics with provided registerer\n95: \n96: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `RecordCleanup(kind string, duration time.Duration, err error)` method in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n97:   - Increment appropriate counter based on kind\n98:   - Record duration in histogram\n99:   - Increment error counter if err != nil\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 398. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 |\n| Module | `pkg/agentd` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Configuration Structure (`config.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n  - Define package `agentd` with required imports\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `CleanupConfig` struct in `pkg/agentd/config.go`","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775863376972,"end":1775863376983}}}}
