{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863415217,"sessionID":"ses_2864be159ffehrySNsT9JNg1Wc","part":{"id":"prt_d79b52d85001T1uNsf9Pl0SEzL","messageID":"msg_d79b5225a001JoUOH6LTzC4BLO","sessionID":"ses_2864be159ffehrySNsT9JNg1Wc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a524d32cd2334615a9251bbc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/verification-report.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/verification-report.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-005 Sandbox 创建处理器 - Verification Report\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: **Status**: ❌ **NOT FULLY COMPLIANT** - Several critical gaps identified\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Spec Requirements vs Implementation\n10: \n11: ### 1. Client-Go Typed Client Interface\n12: \n13: **Spec Requirement** (`deployment/client-go.md`):\n14: ```go\n15: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n16:     Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n17:     Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n18:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n19:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n20:     DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n21:     Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n22:     List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n23:     Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n24:     Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n25:     AgentRuntimeExpansion\n26: }\n27: ```\n28: \n29: **Implementation Status**: ✅ **PARTIALLY IMPLEMENTED**\n30: \n31: The implementation uses `dynamic.Interface` instead of typed client:\n32: - `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/agent_runtime.go:28` - Uses `dynamic.NamespaceableResourceInterface`\n33: - `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/code_interpreter.go:27` - Uses `dynamic.NamespaceableResourceInterface`\n34: \n35: **Gap**: No typed client implementation exists. The code relies on dynamic client which doesn't provide type safety.\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ### 2. Lister Interfaces\n40: \n41: **Spec Requirement** (`deployment/client-go.md`):\n42: ```go\n43: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n44:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n45:     AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n46:     AgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n47: }\n48: \n49: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n50:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n51:     Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n52:     AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n53: }\n54: ```\n55: \n56: **Implementation Status**: ⚠️ **CUSTOM IMPLEMENTATION**\n57: \n58: Located in `pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_processor.go:56-67`:\n59: ```go\n60: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n61:     AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n62: }\n63: \n64: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n65:     Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n66: }\n67: ```\n68: \n69: **Gap**: \n70: - Missing `List(selector labels.Selector)` method in both interfaces\n71: - Missing expansion interfaces (`AgentRuntimeListerExpansion`, `AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion`)\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ### 3. Informer Types\n76: \n77: **Spec Requirement** (`deployment/client-go.md`):\n78: ```go\n79: type AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n80:     Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n81:     Lister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n82: }\n83: ```\n84: \n85: **Implementation Status**: ❌ **NOT IMPLEMENTED**\n86: \n87: - `pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go:67` references `runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer` which does not exist\n88: - **Build Error**: `undefined: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer`\n89: \n90: **Gap**: Informer interfaces are referenced but not defined anywhere in the codebase.\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ### 4. REST Resource Plurals\n95: \n96: **Spec Requirement** (`deployment/client-go.md`):\n97: - AgentRuntime: `agentruntimes`\n98: - CodeInterpreter: `codeinterpreters`\n99: \n100: **Implementation Status**: ✅ **CORRECT**\n101: \n102: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` should define these (verified via handler usage)\n103: - `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/agent_runtime.go:28` uses `\"agentruntimes\"`\n104: - `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/code_interpreter.go:27` uses `\"codeinterpreters\"`\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### 5. Sandbox Processor Core Functions\n109: \n110: **Implementation Status**: ✅ **IMPLEMENTED**\n111: \n112: Located in `pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_processor.go`:\n113: \n114: | Function | Status | Notes |\n115: |----------|--------|-------|\n116: | `GenerateSessionID()` | ✅ | Line 109-114 |\n117: | `BuildSandboxObject()` | ✅ | Line 139-237 |\n118: | `BuildCodeInterpreterSandbox()` | ✅ | Line 269-320 |\n119: | `BuildSandboxClaimObject()` | ✅ | Line 239-266 |\n120: | `CreateSandbox()` | ✅ | Line 383-467 |\n121: | `resolvePodIP()` | ✅ | Line 322-367 |\n122: | `rollback()` | ✅ | Line 469-473 |\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ### 6. Sandbox Creation Handler\n127: \n128: **Implementation Status**: ✅ **IMPLEMENTED**\n129: \n130: | Handler | Endpoint | Status |\n131: |---------|----------|--------|\n132: | `HandleAgentRuntimeCreate` | `POST /v1/agent-runtime` | ✅ Line 44-101 |\n133: | `HandleCodeInterpreterCreate` | `POST /v1/code-interpreter` | ✅ Line 104-164 |\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## Test Results\n138: \n139: ### Passing Tests ✅\n140: - All handler tests (`agent_runtime_test.go`, `code_interpreter_test.go`)\n141: - All response tests (`response/response_test.go`)\n142: - Basic processor tests:\n143:   - `TestRandString`\n144:   - `TestGetAgentRuntime`\n145:   - `TestGetCodeInterpreter`\n146:   - `TestBuildEntryPoints`\n147:   - `TestResolvePodIP`\n148: \n149: ### Failing Tests ❌\n150: - `TestBuildSandboxObject` - **FAILS** (3 assertions fail)\n151:   - Line 235: session-id label not set correctly\n152:   - Line 236: app label not set correctly  \n153:   - Lines 245-246: command/args type mismatch (expected `[]interface{}`, got `[]string`)\n154: \n155: - `TestBuildCodeInterpreterSandbox` - **FAILS** (1 assertion fails)\n156:   - Line 272: session-id label not set correctly\n157: \n158: ### Build Errors ❌\n159: ```\n160: pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go:67:27: undefined: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer\n161: pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go:75:27: undefined: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer\n162: ```\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ## API Contracts Verification\n167: \n168: ### Request/Response Format\n169: \n170: **CreateSandboxRequest** (`types/sandbox_types.go:9-14`):\n171: ```go\n172: type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n173:     Kind      string            `json:\"kind\"`\n174:     Name      string            `json:\"name\"`\n175:     Namespace string            `json:\"namespace\"`\n176:     Labels    map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n177: }\n178: ```\n179: ✅ Matches usage in handlers\n180: \n181: **CreateSandboxResponse** (`types/sandbox_types.go:34-39`):\n182: ```go\n183: type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n184:     SessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n185:     SandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n186:     SandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n187:     EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n188: }\n189: ```\n190: ✅ Correctly populated by handlers\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ## Critical Issues\n195: \n196: ### 1. Missing Client-Go Generated Code ❌\n197: The spec describes a complete generated client-go library structure, but:\n198: - No `client-go/` directory exists\n199: - No typed clients (`AgentRuntimeInterface`, `CodeInterpreterInterface`)\n200: - No informer factories\n201: - No lister implementations (only custom interfaces)\n202: \n203: ### 2. Informer Type References Without Definition ❌\n204: `routes.go` references undefined informer types causing build failures.\n205: \n206: ### 3. Test Failures ⚠️\n207: Two critical test failures indicate bugs in `BuildSandboxObject` and `BuildCodeInterpreterSandbox`:\n208: - Labels are not being copied correctly from runtime/interpreter objects\n209: - Type conversion issues with command/args slices\n210: \n211: ### 4. Expansion Interfaces Missing ⚠️\n212: No expansion interfaces defined for listers (though this is lower priority).\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## Recommendations\n217: \n218: ### Immediate (P0)\n219: 1. **Fix build errors**: Either define informer interfaces or remove references in `routes.go`\n220: 2. **Fix test failures**: Debug label copying in `BuildSandboxObject` and `BuildCodeInterpreterSandbox`\n221: 3. **Fix type conversions**: Ensure command/args are converted to `[]interface{}` properly\n222: \n223: ### Short-term (P1)\n224: 4. **Generate client-go code**: Run `make gen-client` to generate typed clients, informers, and listers\n225: 5. **Add missing lister methods**: Implement `List(selector)` in custom lister interfaces or use generated ones\n226: \n227: ### Long-term (P2)\n228: 6. **Add expansion interfaces**: Define expansion interfaces for future extensibility\n229: 7. **Add Watch support**: Currently not implemented in handlers\n230: 8. **Add UpdateStatus support**: Required for status subresource updates\n231: \n232: ---\n233: \n234: ## Conclusion\n235: \n236: The **core sandbox creation functionality is implemented** (processor, handlers, routes), but the **client-go infrastructure described in the spec is NOT implemented**. The code currently uses dynamic client as a workaround, which works but lacks type safety.\n237: \n238: **Compliance Score**: ~60%\n239: - Core logic: ✅ Implemented\n240: - Test coverage: ⚠️ Partial (2 failing tests)\n241: - Client-go spec: ❌ Not implemented\n242: - Build status: ❌ Failing\n\n(End of file - total 242 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-005 Sandbox 创建处理器 - Verification Report\n\n## Summary\n\n**Status**: ❌ **NOT FULLY COMPLIANT** - Several critical gaps identified\n\n---\n\n## Spec Requirements vs Implementation\n\n### 1. Client-Go Typed Client Interface\n\n**Spec Requirement** (`deployment/client-go.md`):\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n    Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/verification-report.md","time":{"start":1775863415198,"end":1775863415215}}}}
